This memorandum, addressed to the Secretary of State, delegates certain authorities under the Foreign Assistance Act of 1961 to provide immediate military assistance to Ukraine. The delegated authorities include the determination of whether it is necessary to provide up to $250 million in assistance without regard to any provision of law, and the authority to direct the drawdown of up to $350 million in defense articles and services, military education, and training. The memorandum is signed by President Joseph R. Biden Jr. and directs the publication of this memorandum in the Federal Register.